issues.title: Pre-Catalytic Converter Failure
issues.description: The pre-catalytic converter fails prematurely, often breaking apart and sending debris into the main catalytic converter, causing engine damage and poor performance.
issues.fix_description: Replace pre-catalytic converter and main catalytic converter if contaminated. Some owners opt for aftermarket headers to eliminate the pre-cat.
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance, avoid short trips that don't allow engine to fully warm up, use quality fuel

issues.title: Oil Burning and Consumption
issues.description: Excessive oil consumption due to worn piston rings, valve stem seals, or PCV system issues, particularly in higher mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace valve stem seals, PCV valve, or rebuild engine depending on severity. Regular oil top-ups for minor consumption.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid over-revving cold engine, check oil levels frequently

issues.title: Power Steering Rack Failure
issues.description: Power steering rack develops internal leaks causing loss of power steering assist and potential steering issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace power steering rack and pinion assembly, flush power steering system
issues.prevention: Regular power steering fluid changes, avoid hitting curbs or potholes hard

issues.title: Convertible Top Hydraulic Cylinder Failure
issues.description: Hydraulic cylinders that operate the convertible top fail, causing the top to operate slowly or not at all.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty hydraulic cylinders, check and top off hydraulic fluid, inspect lines for leaks
issues.prevention: Regular operation of convertible top, keep hydraulic system maintained

issues.title: Engine Mount Deterioration
issues.description: Engine mounts, particularly the rear mount, deteriorate causing excessive engine vibration and movement.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn engine mounts, typically rear mount fails first
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches, regular inspection of mounts

issues.title: Timing Chain Tensioner Issues
issues.description: Timing chain tensioner fails causing timing chain slack, which can lead to timing issues and potential engine damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace timing chain tensioner, inspect timing chain for stretch, replace if necessary
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid over-revving engine

issues.title: Water Pump Failure
issues.description: Water pump fails causing coolant leaks and potential overheating, common issue as vehicles age.
symptoms: Whining noise from front of engine
issues.fix_description: Replace water pump, thermostat, and flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, maintain proper coolant levels

issues.title: Oxygen Sensor Failure
issues.description: Oxygen sensors fail causing poor fuel economy, rough idle, and emissions issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty oxygen sensors, clear diagnostic codes
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, regular maintenance, avoid oil burning issues

issues.title: Clutch Master Cylinder Failure
issues.description: Clutch master cylinder develops internal leaks causing clutch pedal to feel spongy or go to the floor.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch master cylinder and slave cylinder, bleed clutch system
issues.prevention: Regular clutch fluid changes, avoid riding the clutch

issues.title: Brake Caliper Sticking
issues.description: Brake calipers stick due to corrosion or worn seals, causing uneven brake wear and reduced braking performance.
symptoms: Vehicle pulls to one side when braking
issues.fix_description: Rebuild or replace brake calipers, replace brake pads and rotors if damaged
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, avoid letting vehicle sit for extended periods

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: Fuel pump fails causing engine stalling, no-start conditions, or poor performance under load.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly, replace fuel filter
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above quarter full, use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Ignition Coil Failure
issues.description: Individual ignition coils fail causing misfires and poor engine performance.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed ignition coil(s), replace spark plugs if necessary
issues.prevention: Regular spark plug replacement, avoid carbon buildup

editorial.tagline: Pure mid-engine thrills without the supercar price
editorial.hero_blurb: The MR2 Spyder stripped away everything unnecessary, leaving only what matters: mid-engine balance, open-air freedom, and Toyota reliability. This is driving purity distilled into its most essential form.
editorial.essence: The third-generation MR2 abandoned power wars for something more precious—perfect weight distribution and communicative handling in a package light enough to dance. It's proof that 140 horsepower can deliver more smiles per gallon than cars with twice the power.
editorial.heritage: Born from Toyota's mid-engine sports car lineage that began with the original MR2 in 1984, the Spyder represented a philosophical shift toward minimalism. While its predecessors grew heavier and more complex, the Spyder returned to the original lightweight sports car ethos.
editorial.design_philosophy: Toyota's engineers embraced the 'less is more' philosophy, creating a convertible-only design that prioritized driver engagement over raw performance. Every component was scrutinized for weight savings while maintaining the mid-engine layout that made the MR2 legendary.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a factory racing machine, the MR2 Spyder found success in amateur motorsports, particularly autocross and track days where its balanced chassis and predictable handling characteristics allowed drivers to explore limits safely.
editorial.engine_character: The 1ZZ-FED engine is eager and rev-happy, delivering its modest power with a linear, naturally-aspirated character that rewards high-rpm enthusiasm. It's not about brute force—it's about keeping the engine singing in its sweet spot.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 5-speed manual offers precise, short throws with a mechanical directness that connects you to the drivetrain. Each shift feels purposeful, with gates that guide your hand exactly where it needs to go.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Mid-engine physics creates an inherently balanced platform that rotates beautifully through corners. The chassis communicates every road surface change while remaining forgiving enough for spirited driving without intimidation.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic power steering delivers genuine road feel with appropriate weight that builds naturally through corners. The quick ratio makes the car feel eager to change direction, translating driver inputs with mechanical precision.
editorial.brake_confidence: Four-wheel disc brakes provide strong, consistent stopping power with excellent pedal feel. The balanced weight distribution means no dramatic nose-diving under hard braking, maintaining composure when you need it most.
editorial.sound_signature: The 1.8L produces an honest four-cylinder note that grows more aggressive under acceleration. With the top down, you hear every mechanical symphony—from intake induction to exhaust note—creating an intimate audio experience.
editorial.ideal_owner: Perfect for driving purists who value handling precision over straight-line speed, weekend canyon carvers who appreciate mechanical simplicity, and enthusiasts seeking an affordable entry into mid-engine exotica.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily commuters needing practicality, power seekers wanting big horsepower numbers, or anyone requiring significant cargo space or all-weather capability.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for examples with maintenance records, as the 1ZZ engine is robust but requires regular care. Pre-cat failure can damage engines, so verify this common issue has been addressed or prevented.
